=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Selectively monoprotect cyclohexane-1,3-diol (e.g., TBSCl, imidazole) to give mono-TBS-protected cyclohexane-1,3-diol. | Step 2: React 1-bromo-3,5-difluoro-4-hydroxybenzene with the free alcohol of this mono-protected diol under Mitsunobu conditions (PPh3/DIAD or DEAD) to form 1-bromo-3,5-difluoro-4-(3-TBSO-cyclohexyloxy)benzene. | Step 3: Deprotect the TBS group (e.g., TBAF) to give 1-bromo-3,5-difluoro-4-(3-hydroxycyclohexyloxy)benzene. | Step 4: In parallel, oxidize 1-bromo-4-(methylthio)benzene to 1-bromo-4-(methylsulfonyl)benzene (mCPBA or Oxone), then convert it to 4-(methylsulfonyl)phenylboronic acid or the corresponding Bpin ester by Miyaura borylation (B2pin2, Pd catalyst, KOAc). | Step 5: Couple 1-bromo-3,5-difluoro-4-(3-hydroxycyclohexyloxy)benzene with 4-(methylsulfonyl)phenylboronic acid/Bpin by Suzuki coupling (Pd(PPh3)4 or Pd(dppf)Cl2, base) to furnish CS(=O)(=O)c1ccc(-c2cc(F)c(OC3CCCC(O)C3)c(F)c2)cc1.

